Description: Shoulder and body sherd of Corinthian black-figured pottery globular aryballos; exterior: on shoulder, band of tongues (only traces remaining) bounded below by two bands; below, black-figure decoration consisting of head, upper chest (in added red) and right upper arm of dancing bearded male, to right; part of incised blob rosette as filling ornament.
Curator's comments: Venit gives the wrong registration number (1924,1201.1274) with the correct number as an alternative, both of which are also given by Möller.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 68, no. A57)
Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 221, no.5)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GB.136) (Phase 1)
